<br>
 A nuclear electric propulsion ramjet is a possible <br>
solution to the problem of getting around the limitations <br>
of rocketry. A ramjet unlike a rocket is not subject to <br>
the rocket equation. It can accelerate indefinitely for as <br>
long as it  energy supply, and its equipment will last.<br>
 <br>
We could in principle design a nuclear electric ramjet <br>
starship that is powered by breeder type nuclear fission reactors. We could breed enough new atomic fuel in the<br>
 cores of the breeder type atomic reactors to last us  for<br>
 centurys or mellinea of crewed space flight. <br>
<br>
 This means that the nuclear electric  ramjet starship even with a low acceleration rate of 10 to the -2 gs , or 10 to the  -3 gs could accelerate indefinitely until it approaches<br>
 the velocity of light in space flight.<br>
<br>
 We might create an electromagnetic ram scoop that can collect a few grams of reaction mass per second from space.<br>
The mass collected would then be used as propellant inside<br>
of nuclear electric ion or plasma rocket engines.<br>
<br>
The ramjet starship could be a multigenerational vessel or it could be a sleeper ship if a medicaly  safe method of suspended animation for use by  humans can be found.<br>
<br>
At 10 to the -2 gs it would take 75 years of acceleration to attain 72 % of light velocity which is the practical equivelent of light speed because of the relatavistic gamma factor of<br>
 1.414 which occurrs at .72 C. At 10 to the -2 gs it would take 10 years to reach .10 C (ten percent of light velocity )<br>
<br>
